      "id": "finding:young2021_no_power_spectra_diff",
      "type": "Finding",
      "name": "No cross-tradition EEG power-spectra differences (Young et al. 2021)",
      "description": "In a direct six-tradition comparison (shamatha, vipassana, zazen, dzogchen, tonglen, visualization) against a shared mind-wandering control, Lempel-Ziv complexity differed between meditation and mind-wandering generally, but there were no significant power-spectra differences between the six meditation styles themselves; the authors attribute this partly to between-group heterogeneity and note only exploratory (not confirmatory) evidence of inter-practice differences.",
      "implication": "directly cautions against reading ORTHOGONAL_TO edges in this graph as implying cleanly separable low-level EEG signatures; orthogonality here is best read as phenomenological/doctrinal, with neural separability an open empirical question rather than an established fact",
